\begin_layout Itemize
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

Some of you have wondered which formulas that you are supposed to know for
 the final exam.
 I expect you to know all the formulas that appear in the Key Concepts throughou
t the required readings (see http://www.sfu.ca/~cmuris/2014-Summer-333/Course-sche
dule.pdf, which is now in its final version).
 Exceptions are:
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
The formulas in Key Concept 4.4 - Although it is not mentioned in the Key
 Concepts, I do expect you to know the formulas for the R-squared, both
 in the context of Chapter 4 and in Chapter 6 (see, for example, p.
 193) - Key concept 14.3: you only need to understand this for p=1.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Furthermore, let me give you a heads-up that calculators will not be allowed
 during the exam.
 More instructions about the exam will follow closer to the day of the final.
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset


\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
Write on paper: name, SFU ID, Tutorial number
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
What to do when you are sick: see syllabus
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Bags, jackets, hats, headphones: put in front
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Allowed on desk: pen, calculator, SFU ID, something to eat+drink
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Not allowed: anything else: pencil cases, erasers, pencils, non-graphical
 calculator, phone, ruler
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Toilet break: pre-assigned window of 30 minutes somewhere in the middle
 ??
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Stress that they should limit asking questions to invigilators during midterm/ex
am
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Finish before 20 minutes before end: come forward with SFU ID to hand it
 in; finish later: raise your hand and we will come and pick it up
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Hand in: question sheet *and* answer sheet, with your name and ID written
 on both
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
R: tested on knowledge used for hand-in assignments
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection

\series bold
Exam procedure
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
From Summer 2015, we will have two rooms for each test.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\series bold
Before
\series default
 the exam
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Students have been assigned a row.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
From Test 2: The suspicious people are in row A.
 From then on, the students are assigned to rows 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

randomly
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

, which secretly means 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

by midterm score
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

.
 Best-scoring students are in the back.
 If there is some suspicion of cheating from before, we put those students
 in front, too.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Make sure that they are in the right row (row-wise signature sheets)
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Shuffle the exams and make exam/booklet combinations.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Make sure that only the allowed items are on their desk
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Make sure they are lined up in columns, too, and not too close together
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
One person at the top of the room, helping students find rows L and higher
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\series bold
During
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Only English: speaking non-English will get me in trouble.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
?No bathroom breaks
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Answer minimally, to discourage questions
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Questions disrupt the surrounding students
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Signature sheets are by row.
 We will go and collect signatures throughout the exam.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Until one hour before end, students should get up and hand in exam.
 After that, they should remain seated and we will come to collect.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\series bold
After
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
When students hand in exams, make sure that they hand in both the question
 sheet and the answer sheet.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
?Make one pile per version (A-B-C-D).
 There are 4 versions.
 B-D are obtained through shuffling A.
\end_layout

