\begin_layout Enumerate
Occasionally teach/challenge top students
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Limit work for TA's who should be doing their research
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Contain cheating
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Subsection
Common duties
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Here is what I expect everybody to do.
 You're a Lab TA and/or a Tutorial TA.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Hold office hours.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Invigilation.
 There are three tests, no final.
 Invigilation of exams: check course website and your schedules.
 It is your responsibility to find a replacement.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Grading tests and assignments.
 You are in charge of grading, the spreadsheet.
 I can help with dividing up the work, if you ask.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Review session.
 
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
Organize and host the review session for each test.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Duration: one hour.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
I will be there, too, but just for 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

authority
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Workflow for final grade:
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
After initial grading, you send me the spreadsheet.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Students can plead for regrading by talking to a TA, during review session.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
The TA will no longer have the power to change the grade.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
If the TA finds the plead reasonable, they can encourage the student to
 fill out the regrading request (see form on website).
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
They have to write down SFU ID, name, and tutorial number, and state reason
 for regrading.
 They sign it, and put it in my mailbox.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
If successful, I will then update the spreadsheet.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\end_deeper
\begin_layout Subsection
Lab TA
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
You need to familiarize yourself with R.
 [Books/pdf: see website?]
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Organize and host labs after hand-in assignment 1 is posted
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Grading: it makes sense to grade hand-in assignments.
 We can work on a strategy to reduce the amount of work.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Organize distribution of hand-in assignments back to the students.
 Perhaps distribute them to tutorial TAs for return during tutorials.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
!Let's collaborate on a procedure and format for handing it in that reduces
 grading time and that may help prevent cheating.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
Tutorial TA
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Tutorials are every week (except for week 1)
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
Will tell you about which problems on our weekly meeting.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Formulate your own answers to the questions.
 Check with me if you do not understand.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Email me very short answers before you first tutorial.
 I will publish those answers.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
Tutorial organization
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
Walk around and help students answer the questions: no or almost no BB time;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
HELP, do not TEACH, and do NOT give the answers
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
[idea: saves you time because you do not have to prepare written answers.
 helps the students because only practice will make them understand]
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Course materials should not be reviewed: this is practice time;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
If you spot a subquestion that everybody has, announce that you will discuss
 it on the BB
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
Frequency and duration of tutorials
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
Do not cancel the ones after the midterm, after hand-in's, or on the last
 day of classes (legal).
 I can try to find something to do for the students if we find that attendance
 is low.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Do not leave before the end of the tutorial, unless all the students leave
 first: they have the right to use this time to work on the PS and get your
 assistance;
\end_layout

\end_deeper
